eanings":["form of the Greek name <i>Andreas</i>, a short form of any of various compound names derived from <i>andr-</i> ‘man, warrior’. In the New Testament this is the name of the first disciple to be called by Jesus. After the Resurrection,  St Andrew  preached in Asia Minor and Greece. He is traditionally believed to have been crucified at Patras in Achaia. He was one of the most popular saints of the Middle Ages and was adopted as the patron of Scotland, Russia, and Greece. It has long been among the most popular boys' names in the English-speaking world, especially in Scotland. Its popularity in England was further enhanced by its use as a British royal name for  Prince Andrew  (  b. 1960 ), the Duke of York."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Andrew Lyle was born in 1377, in Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Aaron Lyle, was 25 and his mother, Lady Catherine Kilmarnock Of Kilmamock, was 25. He married Catherine Boyd in 1393, in Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died in 1405, in his hometown, at the age of 28, and was buried in Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1377–1405":"1377–1405","1375–1405":"1375–1405","1395–1439":"1395–1439","1404–1439":"1404–1439","–Male":"Surnud","1352–1439":"1352–1439","1352–1387":"1352–1387","1404":"1404","1377":"1377","1387":"1387","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1395":"1395","1393":"1393","1 January 1395":"1. jaanuar 1395","1439":"1439","1405":"1405","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Kilmarnock, , Ayrshire, Scotland":"Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayrshire, , , Scotland":"Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1377–1405":"1377–1405","1375–1405":"1375–1405","1395–1439":"1395–1439","1404–1439":"1404–1439","–Male":"Kuollut","1352–1439":"1352–1439","1352–1387":"1352–1387","1404":"1404","1377":"1377","1387